The paper deals with algorithmic pricing, which is a problem in game theory (cs.GT) and involves computational techniques (cs.DS). The use of Bayesian distributions and mechanism design also suggests categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economics and computation (cs.EC). Finally, the paper proposes a constant approximation algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
